<p>Replit has decent online editors. I use it mainly for Python and NodeJS web projects when I’m using my phone, but it does have Java, C++, C# and others as well.</p>
<p>Its convenient because I can start a project on my phone. When I have a few minutes I can  work on it, then still pick it back up on my PC later through a web browser no downloads needed.</p>
<p>Long term yes install a JDK and a true IDE (blueJ is the least helpful IDE, which is good and bad). VSCode can do Java, but Eclipse or IntelliJ is what most developers would say they use. Android Studio is built on IntelliJ as the default IDE for Android development. It’s powerful and helpful, but can feel daunting when you just want to learn the basics of code.</p>
